\sum \limits_{n=1}^{\infty} \dfrac{n^{k-1}}{n^k+c}
f\left(x\right) = \dfrac{x^{k-1}}{x^k+c}
f^{\prime}\left(x\right) = \dfrac{\left(k-1\right)x^{k-2}x^{k}-kx^{k-1}x^{k-1}}{\left(x^k+c\right)^2} < 0
f^{\prime}\left(x\right) = \dfrac{\left(k-1\right)x^{k-2}x^{k}-kx^{k-1}x^{k-1}}{\left(x^k+c\right)^2} =\dfrac{\left(k-1\right)x^{2k-2}-kx^{2k-2}}{\left(x^k+c\right)^2}=\dfrac{x^{2k-2}(\left(k-1\right)-k)}{\left(x^k+c\right)^2}=\dfrac{-x^{2k-2}}{\left(x^k+c\right)^2}< 0
x^{2k-2}
f'(x)
